title: Big Deal Comedy Club - Downham Market
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Big Deal Comedy is bringing some much needed comedy to Downham Market, join East Anglia's award winning comedy club in a night of side splitting laughter.

Whether you're a comedy fanatic or a first timer, the Big Deal Comedy Club promises an evening filled with laughter, joy, and the kind of memories you'll be sharing for years to come. Join us for an incredible night of comedy that transcends the ordinary and leaves you with a smile that lasts long after the final punchline. Get ready to laugh until your cheeks hurt!

The Venue
Downham Market’s striking Town Hall was constructed as a memento of Queen Victoria’s Golden Jubilee in 1887. ​In 2008 the building was put into the care of the Town Council and so it remains today.

The Comedy
Your evening will kick start with Jason Stampe, Big Deal Comedy's resident MC, known all over the UK as a top talent, your night will be off to a brilliant start with him leading the way!

Following Jason will be a trio of the very best comedians on the circuit right now, we keep the names under lock and key until you arrive! As East Anglia's award winning comedy club, you can trust in us in bringing the very best acts with us.

What are you waiting for?

Grab your tickets today! Be a part of the origin story

The doors and bar open at 7pm - grab a drink before securing your preferred seat for the night
Comedy starts at 8pm

title: The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London August-November
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Step into the heart of everyone’s favourite TV show, at the European flagship of The ​FRIENDS™​ Experience.  
​​The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London promises a taste of New York City, and never-before-seen content including “London, baby!” and FRIENDS™ Station. ​ 

Immerse yourself in recreated sets; dance in front of the fountain, peep through the iconic purple door at Rachel and Monica’s apartment, play foosball at Joey and Chandler’s, and take a selfie on the orange couch in Central Perk.  

The Turkey Head – we have it. Phoebe’s New York cab – we have it. The 18-page letter – we have it (front and back!) 

​​Hang out in the FRIENDS™ Station for even more photo opportunities, snacks, and of course, ​coffee​ before hitting up the FRIENDS™ Retail Store. And yes, we’ve got Hugsy and the famous yellow frame waiting for you. ​ 

​​OH.MY.GAWD! The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London. ​

Info:
Every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the historic Camden Eye pub hosts an exciting night of Stand Up Comedy for just £3, featuring a mix of TV comics and rising stars from the acclaimed London Comedy Circuit, all conveniently located right opposite Camden Town Tube station!

Enjoy fast paced funnies, with a new, top secret lineup of amazing comics every time, all performing short sets to keep you constantly entertained. 

Our laughter packed shows have seen comedians, who have had Netflix and Amazon Prime specials, as well as featuring on Live at the Apollo, Conan, QI, Mock the Week, 8 Out of 10 Cats, Taskmaster, Britain's Got Talent, The Lateish Show with Mo Gilligan, Russell Howard's Good News, Would I Lie to You, ITV's The Stand Up Sketch Show and many more!

We are also part of the Get Off Live Comedy initiative aiming to create safe spaces for all comics and audience members to enjoy.

Entry is just £3 or buy a drink ticket, which is basically like getting comedy in your eye for free!

Timings:

Downstairs bar is open from 12pm
Show starts - 7:15pm
Interval - 8:30pm
2nd Half Starts - 8:40m
Show finishes - 9:30pm

Please note that this is an 18+ venue and so please bring a valid form of identification.

For more info, please visit our website - www.comedyinyoureye.com

We look forward to seeing you soon!

"EXCELLENT COMEDY NIGHT WITH FANTASTIC MC'S" - THE EVENING STANDARD

Info:
Every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the historic Camden Eye pub hosts an exciting night of Stand Up Comedy for just £3, featuring a mix of TV comics and rising stars from the acclaimed London Comedy Circuit, all conveniently located right opposite Camden Town Tube station!

Enjoy fast paced funnies, with a new, top secret lineup of amazing comics every time, all performing short sets to keep you constantly entertained. 

Our laughter packed shows have seen comedians, who have had Netflix and Amazon Prime specials, as well as featuring on Live at the Apollo, Conan, QI, Mock the Week, 8 Out of 10 Cats, Taskmaster, Britain's Got Talent, The Lateish Show with Mo Gilligan, Russell Howard's Good News, Would I Lie to You, ITV's The Stand Up Sketch Show and many more!

We are also part of the Get Off Live Comedy initiative aiming to create safe spaces for all comics and audience members to enjoy.

Entry is just £3 or buy a drink ticket, which is basically like getting comedy in your eye for free!

Timings:

Downstairs bar is open from 12pm
Show starts - 7:15pm
Interval - 8:30pm
2nd Half Starts - 8:40m
Show finishes - 9:30pm

Please note that this is an 18+ venue and so please bring a valid form of identification.

For more info, please visit our website - www.comedyinyoureye.com

We look forward to seeing you soon!

Info:
Every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the historic Camden Eye pub hosts an exciting night of Stand Up Comedy for just £3, featuring a mix of TV comics and rising stars from the acclaimed London Comedy Circuit, all conveniently located right opposite Camden Town Tube station!

Enjoy fast paced funnies, with a new, top secret lineup of amazing comics every time, all performing short sets to keep you constantly entertained. 

Our laughter packed shows have seen comedians, who have had Netflix and Amazon Prime specials, as well as featuring on Live at the Apollo, Conan, QI, Mock the Week, 8 Out of 10 Cats, Taskmaster, Britain's Got Talent, The Lateish Show with Mo Gilligan, Russell Howard's Good News, Would I Lie to You, ITV's The Stand Up Sketch Show and many more!

We are also part of the Get Off Live Comedy initiative aiming to create safe spaces for all comics and audience members to enjoy.

Entry is just £3 or buy a drink ticket, which is basically like getting comedy in your eye for free!

Please note that this is an 18+ venue and so please bring a valid form of identification.

For more info, please visit our website - www.comedyinyoureye.com

We look forward to seeing you soon!

title: Gary Meikle - 'NO REFUNDS'
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Ladies & Gentleman! Gary Meikle is back yet again with another self-written, self-deprecating show to leave you all short of breath again. Last year “Papa” as he is becoming more commonly known as, because the 1st ever comedian worldwide without an agent (his choice) to be granted a full working visa for the USA and is keen to keep on showing why. Gary’s tour this year promises to deliver, he will reluctantly share his newer role in life being a kept man, by the lady that kept him of course being his ever-growing smarter granddaughter, Gracie. Who intelligently but more essentially rips the piss out of her Papa daily. A few stories to note are when she blatantly points out that he’s got “moobs”. She also embarrasses him by telling the truth about his tattoos to a stranger that he is trying to impress. She explains in detail how her Papa isn’t THAT famous and how she calls him a bad name without meaning it. There are literally to many Gracie and Papa stories to cover but as usual Gary will go of on tangents and delve into the workings of his on mind. He will tackle subjects such as: rejection issues of men and women, what it was like being a 14-year-old hormonal boy, how it is ok for men to be overtly feminine now, cold showers, mosquitoes on holiday and much more. If you can guarantee one thing from Gary it is that he will work, his 5’8 ass off to make sure everyone that sees him live wants to come back for more. Your laughter makes up for the rejection he suffered in his earlier years, and he will thank you all individually if you choose to come along to his meet and greet, pre-show that he will be doing at every single show again. Love, Gary X 

 
Accessible Info 
There is a lift up to the first floor and a ramp into the studio. You are also welcome to use our fenced-off disabled area at standing events. We also have a disabled toilet but you will need to ask a member of staff for the key. 
Carer Ticket
Carers will not need a physical ticket. So long as you have a ticket for yourself, you are welcome to bring a carer in for free without a ticket as long as you can provide proof of carer status. 
 Other Info - This is a seated event and is allocated on a first come first serve basis. You cannot reserve a seat prior to the doors opening for any reason. If you have any specific seating requirements, please let a member of staff know on the night and they will be happy to help.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.


Read our privacy policy: https://standrews.com/privacy-policy

title: Love Club: Half Day Yoga and Creative Wellbeing Retreat
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join Love Club for a half day yoga and creative wellbeing retreat immersed in the tranquil Hertfordshire countryside. Come and nurture your creative spark, while nourishing your body with mindfulness and movement, to cocoon, and to settle into autumn.

The day will begin with grounding, yoga-based movement and meditation, followed by tea and a welcome circle. The afternoon will be spent immersing ourselves in the grounds of Home Farm (weather dependent), drawing in nature, creative writing and poetry, inspired by our magical surroundings. 

No skills are required for this retreat at all, but come with an open heart and open to exploring your own creativity, and seeing what arises. A full day schedule will be sent around closer to the time.

Love Club is a social enterprise creative wellbeing organisation. They run workshops that inspire you to explore your own innate creativity, and wholeheartedly believe that everyone (yes, everyone!) has immense creative power inside them, and they just need to be given the opportunity to explore.

As a social enterprise, they donate a portion of profits from each event to grassroots charities and organisations. 10% of your ticket price will be donated to Compass Collective, a charity supporting unaccompanied minor refugees and young people to integrate into the UK with theatre, music, film and arts based projects.
Refreshments and veg/an snacks will be provided. Bring a packed lunch. 

Accessibility:
Home Farm is a rural venue, we endeavour to meet all accessibility requirements but we will need to discuss in advance to ensure we are prepared.

Inclement weather may restrict wheelchair access and if this occurs we will offer to transfer your ticket to another date or refund, whichever is preferable.

*If you have accessibility requirements please contact hello@athomefarm.live*

At Home Farm is a season of intimate events taking place over Summer 2024 at Home Farm, Elstree, Borehamwood - accessible by tube and Thameslink on the edge of North London.   If you don't live locally or in London, why not consider staying the night with us in our meadow, at one of Home Farm Glamping's fully furnished yurts or bell tents, as an add on to your ticket.

To keep up to date with all At Home Farm announcements sign up here. 

Location:
Home Farm is a rural location on the edge of London, accessible by tube (Edgware or Stanmore) and Thameslink rail (Elstree & Borehamwood).

Uber, and local cabs service the area, and there is a car park for anyone who wishes to drive.

Further info on the venue can be found here, and Terms and Conditions of Entry can be found here

Booking Fees:
We realise booking fees are frustrating, we don’t incorporate it into the ticket fee so that there’s transparency of where your money is going to. We are a small, independent organisation, and unfortunately we don’t have the capacity to process payments so these booking fees go directly to the ticket agency to cover their administration and fees.

title: The Leo Green Experience Live - London's Greatest Sax Party
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - DO NOT MISS THE MOST EXCITING, INTERACTIVE SAX SHOW AROUND !

The Leo Green Experience will be at QT, in the heart of Covent Garden every Saturday Night - grab your tickets now as they tend to go quickly - it's tables and chairs and plenty of room for partying!

Join Sax legend Leo Green and his incredible band and singers for an amazing, fun, high energy night featuring classics from the last 30 years or so - rearranged and drenched in Leo's inimitable Sax! 

Over the last couple of years, this show has built a reputation as one of the most fun and entertaining shows around:

"We were blown away with the show!" .......“I couldn’t sit still!”  .........“I loved it, I had the best time EVER!”   .....“The vibes were amazing”

Check out Leo and his show on his Social Channels: Instagram or TikTok or Facebook or YouTube


Sax legend Leo Green’s musical prowess has taken him all over the world as saxophonist for everyone from Jack Savoretti to Paul McCartney. Not to mention rock'n'roll icon Jerry Lee Lewis, who once declared him to be “The greatest sax player I have ever worked with.” 

Leo has channelled his talents – together with his little black book of extraordinary contacts – into his exciting stage show, which has become one of London's 'must see' shows.

Leo's shows will play host to an array of ultra-talented musicians and singers - who have worked with everyone from Rita Ora to Aretha Franklin - as they put their own unique jazzy, bluesy, funky and soulful twist on some of the best loved songs of the last 30 or so years.

Everything is woven together by Leo’s inimitable hosting and his trusty sax. Says Leo, “As with all my shows, it's the songs that are the stars; these are the soundtracks that people love to hear and relate to. Bringing the classics to life offers the perfect combination. After all, what could be better than watching, listening and of course SUGGESTING SONGS -  to a band and singers perform with a slice of jazzy soulful Sax, whilst losing yourself in a classic London Club? It doesn’t get much better than this!” 

DON'T MISS OUT....HERE'S WHAT PEOPLE ARE SAYING .........

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: The Leo Green Experience Live - London's Greatest Sax Party
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - DO NOT MISS THE MOST EXCITING, INTERACTIVE SAX SHOW AROUND !

The Leo Green Experience will be at QT, in the heart of Covent Garden every Saturday Night - grab your tickets now as they tend to go quickly - it's tables and chairs and plenty of room for partying!

Join Sax legend Leo Green and his incredible band and singers for an amazing, fun, high energy night featuring classics from the last 30 years or so - rearranged and drenched in Leo's inimitable Sax! 

Over the last couple of years, this show has built a reputation as one of the most fun and entertaining shows around:

"We were blown away with the show!" .......“I couldn’t sit still!”  .........“I loved it, I had the best time EVER!”   .....“The vibes were amazing”

Check out Leo and his show on his Social Channels: Instagram or TikTok or Facebook or YouTube


Sax legend Leo Green’s musical prowess has taken him all over the world as saxophonist for everyone from Jack Savoretti to Paul McCartney. Not to mention rock'n'roll icon Jerry Lee Lewis, who once declared him to be “The greatest sax player I have ever worked with.” 

Leo has channelled his talents – together with his little black book of extraordinary contacts – into his exciting stage show, which has become one of London's 'must see' shows.

Leo's shows will play host to an array of ultra-talented musicians and singers - who have worked with everyone from Rita Ora to Aretha Franklin - as they put their own unique jazzy, bluesy, funky and soulful twist on some of the best loved songs of the last 30 or so years.

Everything is woven together by Leo’s inimitable hosting and his trusty sax. Says Leo, “As with all my shows, it's the songs that are the stars; these are the soundtracks that people love to hear and relate to. Bringing the classics to life offers the perfect combination. After all, what could be better than watching, listening and of course SUGGESTING SONGS -  to a band and singers perform with a slice of jazzy soulful Sax, whilst losing yourself in a classic London Club? It doesn’t get much better than this!” 

DON'T MISS OUT....HERE'S WHAT PEOPLE ARE SAYING .........

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: Comedy in Your Eye - Stand up Comedy - Only £3!
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Quotes and Nominations:
"EXCELLENT COMEDY NIGHT WITH FANTASTIC MC'S" - THE EVENING STANDARD
"MUST BE ONE OF THE BEST COMEDY NIGHTS IN LONDON" - DESIGNMYNIGHT.COM
NOMINATED FOR "BEST COMEDY VENUE" - TIME OUT LOVE LOCAL AWARDS
OVER 500 FIVE STAR REVIEWS ACROSS OUR TICKETING PAGES

Info:
Every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the historic Camden Eye pub hosts an exciting night of Stand Up Comedy for just £3, featuring a mix of TV comics and rising stars from the acclaimed London Comedy Circuit, all conveniently located right opposite Camden Town Tube station!

Enjoy fast paced funnies, with a new, top secret lineup of amazing comics every time, all performing short sets to keep you constantly entertained. 

Our laughter packed shows have seen comedians, who have had Netflix and Amazon Prime specials, as well as featuring on Live at the Apollo, Conan, QI, Mock the Week, 8 Out of 10 Cats, Taskmaster, Britain's Got Talent, The Lateish Show with Mo Gilligan, Russell Howard's Good News, Would I Lie to You, ITV's The Stand Up Sketch Show and many more!

We are also part of the Get Off Live Comedy initiative aiming to create safe spaces for all comics and audience members to enjoy.

Entry is just £3 or buy a drink ticket, which is basically like getting comedy in your eye for free!

Timings:

Downstairs bar is open from 12pm
Show starts - 7:15pm
Interval - 8:30pm
2nd Half Starts - 8:40m
Show finishes - 9:30pm

Please note that this is an 18+ venue and so please bring a valid form of identification.

For more info, please visit our website - www.comedyinyoureye.com

We look forward to seeing you soon!

Sourced from predicthq.com - Back by popular demand, we welcome Josh Katz, published author, and chef-owner of Berber & Q Grill House, Shawarma Bar, and Carmel restaurants, in collaboration with fire-cooking legend Ben Quinn and his Woodfired Canteen team. They will design and prepare a bespoke menu for this long table feast cooked over fire.

These special events take place under our beautiful Kata Tipis that overlook the Home Farm meadows and infamous Oak Tree.

Included in your ticket price:
- A welcome drink
- Pre-dinner nibble
- 3 course seated dinner served on sharing platters

Every seat is filled on the long table, so please note that if you are a group of 1, 3 or 5 for example, one person in your group will be opposite another friendly person from the group next to you.

Further drinks, wine, beer, cocktails, soft drinks and more, will be available to purchase at the event.

If you are Veg/An or have any other allergies or dietary needs, please complete the form here

***We will be unable to cater for allergies and dietary requirements if you have not completed the form.***

Accessibility:

Home Farm is a rural venue, we endeavour to meet all accessibility requirements but we will need to discuss in advance to ensure we are prepared.

Inclement weather may restrict wheelchair access and if this occurs we will offer to transfer your ticket to another date or refund, whichever is preferable.

*If you have accessibility requirements please contact hello@athomefarm.live*

At Home Farmis a season of intimate events taking place over Summer 2024 at Home Farm, Elstree, Borehamwood - accessible by tube and Thameslink on the edge of North London.   If you don't live locally or in London, why not consider staying the night with us in our meadow, at one of Home Farm Glamping's fully furnished yurts or bell tents, as an add on to your ticket.

To keep up to date with all At Home Farm announcements sign up here. 

Location:
Home Farm is a rural location on the edge of London, accessible by tube (Edgware or Stanmore) and Thameslink rail (Elstree & Borehamwood).

Uber, and local cabs service the area, and there is a car park for anyone who wishes to drive.

Further info on the venue can be found here, and Terms and Conditions of Entry can be found here

Booking Fees:
We realise booking fees are frustrating, we don’t incorporate it into the ticket fee so that there’s transparency of where your money is going to. We are a small, independent organisation, and unfortunately we don’t have the capacity to process payments so these booking fees go directly to the ticket agency to cover their administration and fees.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London August-November.
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Step into the heart of everyone’s favourite TV show, at the European flagship of The ​FRIENDS™​ Experience.  
​​The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London promises a taste of New York City, and never-before-seen content including “London, baby!” and FRIENDS™ Station. ​ 

Immerse yourself in recreated sets; dance in front of the fountain, peep through the iconic purple door at Rachel and Monica’s apartment, play foosball at Joey and Chandler’s, and take a selfie on the orange couch in Central Perk.  

The Turkey Head – we have it. Phoebe’s New York cab – we have it. The 18-page letter – we have it (front and back!) 

​​Hang out in the FRIENDS™ Station for even more photo opportunities, snacks, and of course, ​coffee​ before hitting up the FRIENDS™ Retail Store. And yes, we’ve got Hugsy and the famous yellow frame waiting for you. ​ 

​​OH.MY.GAWD! The FRIENDS™ Experience: The One in London. ​

Info:
Every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the historic Camden Eye pub hosts an exciting night of Stand Up Comedy for just £3, featuring a mix of TV comics and rising stars from the acclaimed London Comedy Circuit, all conveniently located right opposite Camden Town Tube station!

Enjoy fast paced funnies, with a new, top secret lineup of amazing comics every time, all performing short sets to keep you constantly entertained. 

Our laughter packed shows have seen comedians, who have had Netflix and Amazon Prime specials, as well as featuring on Live at the Apollo, Conan, QI, Mock the Week, 8 Out of 10 Cats, Taskmaster, Britain's Got Talent, The Lateish Show with Mo Gilligan, Russell Howard's Good News, Would I Lie to You, ITV's The Stand Up Sketch Show and many more!

We are also part of the Get Off Live Comedy initiative aiming to create safe spaces for all comics and audience members to enjoy.

Entry is just £3 or buy a drink ticket, which is basically like getting comedy in your eye for free!

Timings:

Downstairs bar is open from 12pm
Show starts - 7:15pm
Interval - 8:30pm
2nd Half Starts - 8:40m
Show finishes - 9:30pm

Please note that this is an 18+ venue and so please bring a valid form of identification.

For more info, please visit our website - www.comedyinyoureye.com

We look forward to seeing you soon!

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.


Read our privacy policy: https://standrews.com/privacy-policy

title: Guided Walks of the Old Course
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Join an expert guide on a tour of the world's most famous golf course. Walk in the footsteps of icons of the game and experience a player's eye view of the fabled links.

Historic records show that golf has been played in St Andrews for more than 600 years, although many believe the game's origins here date back to the 12th Century. As well as being the birthplace of the game of golf, our tour of the world's most famous Links will give you an insight into the iconic landmarks and a history that is both unique and unparalleled. With the Old Course busy for play six days a week throughout the year, this tour is a great way to soak up the history of the centuries-old fairways without having to secure a coveted tee time.
Monday-Saturday Standard Walking Tour
Enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course (lasts approx. 1hr 15mins). After your tour you can collect your complimentary Old Course scorecard from the Old Course Shop.
NEW: Sunday Premium Tour
Immerse yourself in golfing history with our exclusive Sunday Premium Tour. Included with your Sunday ticket you will enjoy a Guided Walk of the Old Course, followed by a delicious 2-course Sunday Lunch* at Tom Morris Bar & Grill, located in the St Andrews Links Clubhouse. Complete your experience with a visit to one of our official stores to collect your complimentary TravisMathew hat and Old Course scorecard. 
Limited spaces are available, so secure your spot now for an extraordinary Sunday at St Andrews!

* Please allow 1 hour to 1 hour 30 minutes for lunch.
Food & Beverage
To reserve a table at the Tom Morris Bar & Grill in the Links Clubhouse click here.
World Golf Museum
Your ticket also entitles you to purchase a discounted entry* into the R&A World Golf Museum (Current discounted rate: Adult £12.50; Seniors aged 60+ £7.50).*Entry to the museum is subject to availability and the Museum reserves the right to withdraw the offer.
Additional Information

For our wheelchair policy and conditional tour date information, please see the terms and conditions section of our legal page available here.
All tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable. 
If there are no tickets sold for a scheduled Guided Walk this will be subject to cancellation. To avoid disappointment please book online in advance.

title: The Leo Green Experience Live - London's Greatest Sax Party
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - DO NOT MISS THE MOST EXCITING, INTERACTIVE SAX SHOW AROUND !

The Leo Green Experience will be at QT, in the heart of Covent Garden every Saturday Night - grab your tickets now as they tend to go quickly - it's tables and chairs and plenty of room for partying!

Join Sax legend Leo Green and his incredible band and singers for an amazing, fun, high energy night featuring classics from the last 30 years or so - rearranged and drenched in Leo's inimitable Sax! 

Over the last couple of years, this show has built a reputation as one of the most fun and entertaining shows around:

"We were blown away with the show!" .......“I couldn’t sit still!”  .........“I loved it, I had the best time EVER!”   .....“The vibes were amazing”

Check out Leo and his show on his Social Channels: Instagram or TikTok or Facebook or YouTube


Sax legend Leo Green’s musical prowess has taken him all over the world as saxophonist for everyone from Jack Savoretti to Paul McCartney. Not to mention rock'n'roll icon Jerry Lee Lewis, who once declared him to be “The greatest sax player I have ever worked with.” 

Leo has channelled his talents – together with his little black book of extraordinary contacts – into his exciting stage show, which has become one of London's 'must see' shows.

Leo's shows will play host to an array of ultra-talented musicians and singers - who have worked with everyone from Rita Ora to Aretha Franklin - as they put their own unique jazzy, bluesy, funky and soulful twist on some of the best loved songs of the last 30 or so years.

Everything is woven together by Leo’s inimitable hosting and his trusty sax. Says Leo, “As with all my shows, it's the songs that are the stars; these are the soundtracks that people love to hear and relate to. Bringing the classics to life offers the perfect combination. After all, what could be better than watching, listening and of course SUGGESTING SONGS -  to a band and singers perform with a slice of jazzy soulful Sax, whilst losing yourself in a classic London Club? It doesn’t get much better than this!” 

DON'T MISS OUT....HERE'S WHAT PEOPLE ARE SAYING .........

Get ready for the most exhilarating and provocative drag show of the year! Dahli and Evah Destruction are starting their spectacular Carnival of Filth tour in the UK. This is a magical night you won't want to miss —filled with surprises that will have you on the edge of your seats!
SEPT 13 The Clapham Grand.
SEPT 14 Switch Southampton.
SEPT 15 PRYSM Brighton.
SEPT 17 The Fleece Bristol.
SEPT 18 CRUZ 101 Manchester.
SEPT 20 Corporation Sheffield.
SEPT 21 KUDA York.
SEPT 22 Flares Newcastle.
SEPT 27 The Classic Grand Glasgow.
SEPT 28 Shanghai Club Edinburgh.
SEPT 29 The Underworld Camden London.
Join us for a night of unparalleled entertainment featuring jaw-dropping performances and hand selected local support acts that will set the stage ablaze. Experience the raw talent and unfiltered artistry of Dahli and Evah Destruction as they push the boundaries of drag and performance art.
Why You Can't Miss This Show:
- Unrestrained and unapologetic performances by Dahli and Evah Destruction.
- A unique blend of horror, seduction, and glamour.
- Support from top local artists, ensuring an unforgettable night of entertainment.
- An inclusive celebration of individuality, self-expression, and alternative drag culture.
🎟Secure your tickets now for a front-row seat to the most captivating and boundary-pushing drag show of the year. Welcome to the Carnival of Filth—where the bizarre is beautiful, and the filthy is fabulous. ✨️
